<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870518-0055 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Boys Markets Inc.</HL><DD> 05/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BOYSINITIAL STOCK OFFERINGS (INI)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><TEXT>   BOYS MARKETS INC., based in Los Angeles, said it began an initial offering of 1.4 million common shares priced at $10.25 each. Boys, a supermarket chain, said the company is selling 1.2 million shares and shareholders the rest. A spokeswoman for Boys said the offering will bring the company's common shares outstanding to 10.4 million, including stock currently held by management. The company said it will use proceeds to reduce debt and redeem preferred stock issued in connection with the previous management buyout of the company. Merrill Lynch Capital Markets is lead underwriter for the sale. </TEXT></DOC>